Description:
Quality and Style in a Perfect Position
Situated in a unique cul-de-sac with parkland across the road and instant access to Merri Creek trails, this captivating home provides a ready-to-enjoy lifestyle opportunity with its quality internal features and fabulous outdoor entertaining area. Beyond the picket-fenced garden and attractive facade, the home's inviting interior comprises two main bedrooms (one with BIRs) and modern central bathroom, light-filled lounge and adjoining dining room leading through to the family/meals area and updated timber-cabinet kitchen with dishwasher. Add to this ducted heating and split-system air conditioning, polished hardwood floors, laundry and second WC. Step outside to a fabulous undercover entertaining deck with cafe blinds and enclosed outdoor spa, as well as a versatile studio/office (or third bedroom), workshop/storeroom and established gardens, plus front carport and additional off-street parking space. Zoned to Coburg High School, it's also walking distance to Murray Road buses, Coburg Lake and swimming pool, as well as easy access to Nicholson Street trams and Coburg Hill Shopping Centre. Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
Insights: 22 Hutchison Place, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
A Serene Garden Haven
The period pedigree of this two-bedroom Art Deco residence shines through thoughtfully updated interiors to deliver a private haven set amongst garden surrounds. Decorative ceilings, picture rails, leadlight windows and gleaming timber floors grace this bright airy home. A spacious lounge flows to a country-inspired kitchen/meals area featuring a 800mm Emilia range and quaint open shelving. Picture windows frame leafy views to an established courtyard garden offering alfresco entertaining, while the well-positioned laundry does double duty as a butler's pantry with dishwasher. Privately zoned bedrooms – master with garden views and BIRs - share a central bathroom, while year-round comfort is assured with split system heating/cooling. A short stroll to Batman and Coburg train stations, Coburg North Village shopping precinct, Coburg North Primary School, Sydney Road shops and cafés, Farmer's Market, parks, and the Merri Creek bike trail. Inspection will impress!

Description:
Enchanting Edwardian Bijou
A welcoming haven in an enticing locale, this Edwardian Bijou marries original features with more contemporary additions including a third bedroom. Open design flows from a living room, with gas wall furnace and wood heater, past a kitchen with a gas cooktop, pyrolitic oven, dishwasher and timber cabinetry, to a dining area. The productive rear garden invites alfresco meals and a pedestrian gate accesses a rear ROW. Baltic pine floorboards, leadlight and timber fretwork are complemented by evaporative cooling, solar panels, storage and CCTV. Schools, trams, local shops, cafes, Miinot Gelato and Shore Reserve are a stroll and the home is zoned to Strathmore College.

Inspired design, luxurious living.
Flowing, refined and full of features, this four bedroom, two bathroom, period inspired residence shines. 900mm appliances and stone surfaces grace the gourmet kitchen, complemented by a large dining area, wet bar and covered outdoor entertaining area. Description:
Shore To Impress
Conveniently placed close to Coburg Lake Reserve, Batman train station, Gaffney Street shops and a selection of reputable schools, this captivating 1950's three bedroom home invites you to move in and enjoy in this truly tranquil location.
Freshly painted and originally designed to encourage abundant natural light, the interior exudes a feeling of spaciousness.
The double fronted dwelling presents three living zones to accommodate all occasions.
A large lounge/dining area overlooks a covered front patio and makes an ideal formal living zone, whilst the central kitchen/meals domain, boasts a full complement of appliances amid generous cabinetry.
The additional sunroom invites family entertaining and promises glorious relaxation in the winter sun while awning blinds block out the heat in the hotter months.
The three bedrooms are double in size for comfortable accommodation, and share the family bathroom.
Ample off street parking is available via the side driveway which includes a carport and garage.
Finalising the package are evaporative air conditioning, gas heating and a separate laundry.

Description:
Lovingly Maintained, Winningly Positioned
You'll be hooked on this meticulously presented three bedroom home, just moments to Harmony Park, transport, schools, buzzing Coburg North Village, O'Heas Bakery and cafes. Sunlit, elevated and immediately comfortable this much loved abode resides on approximately 483m2, has the appeal of retro styling and will richly reward modern enhancements. Tiled floors feature throughout and spacious design incorporates a large living room with gas wall furnace and fully equipped kitchen/meals hosting a Chef stove with gas cooktop and fan forced oven, dishwasher, rangehood, pantry, leadlight and timber cabinetry, tiled splashbacks and decent counter space. Three double bedrooms share a sparkling vintage pink bathroom with a shower and separate bath, and there's a laundry and separate toilet. The rear yard has space to grow delicious veggies and alfresco dining potential, roller shutters enhance security and insulation, and parking is taken care of by a long side driveway and garage.

Description:
Versatile Style in the Heart of Coburg
On a sizeable block of land with established gardens all-round, this double-front Victorian presents an impeccable environment of space and style along with outstanding potential to further enhance and expand (STCA). Previously extended floorplan boasts a wide hallway accessing three large bedrooms (two with BIRs) and central bathroom, elegant formal lounge and dining room (potential fourth bedroom), plus a light-filled living area and adjoining kitchen with dishwasher, timber cabinetry and breakfast bar. Other features of the home include high ornate ceilings, ducted heating and split-system a/c, large laundry with ample storage cupboards, as well as a sunny backyard with established gardens, watertanks and irrigation system, secure carport via ROW. In a blissfully quiet location well south of Bell Street, the best of Coburg is at your fingertips including trains, trams and buses, renowned shops and major supermarkets, cafes and restaurants, as well as easy access to local parks and schools.
Insights: 14 Mayfield Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Big rooms, period features and wide side drive on 511m2 allotment.
Very solid and sound brick family home with large rooms, period features and flowing floor plan is immediately livable now or easily updated to suit your needs. Wide side drive for 3 cars ,brick garage with workshop , store and deep North facing rear yard. Short walk to Nicholson Street Tram, De Chene Reserve and Merri Creek walking trails make this home an easy, convenient choice.
Accommodation Includes:
• Wide entrance hallway
• Three large bedrooms with ornate ceilings
• Central bathroom with separate shower and bath tub
• Large formal lounge room with period features/ceiling
• Formal dining room
• Adjoining kitchen which overlooks rear yard
• Massive laundry/ study/ 4th bedroom/utility room
• Separate W/C
Featuring: Under house room with storage cupboards ,wide side drive to garage, gas ducted heating, evaporative cooling, security roller shutters and heaps of period features to enjoy.
A wonderful opportunity to purchase a much loved family home in this central location with transport, parkland, shopping and schools all within a convenient stroll.

Description:
A Smart Choice
Quietly centred within a set of three, this two bedroom villa is a smart choice for investors, downsizers and market entrants. A spacious floor plan is introduced by a well scaled open plan living domain inclusive of a kitchen boasting a full complement of stainless steel appliances. The adjoining courtyard enjoys a favourable northerly aspect which lights up the large alfresco deck. A tidy central bathroom separates two double bedrooms, both with generous mirrored built-in wardrobes. There's also a separate laundry, ducted heating and a remote controlled garage accommodates the car. Promoting a healthy lifestyle, it's just a stroll to Merri Creek Trail and surrounding parkland, Nicholson Street tram service and minutes to schools plus Sydney Road shops and cafes.

Description:
Arguably The Most Affordable Home in Coburg
Open to improvement whilst presenting an exceedingly rare opportunity this three bedroom single fronted Victorian home, is located in a highly sought-after pocket of Coburg, just a short walk from Coburg North Primary, O'Hea Street Bakery, local shops and public transport.
Offering an abundance of original features including high ornate ceilings and wrought iron fretwork; this amazing property is ready to be restored to its former glory, or demolish & redesign (STCA).
Reconfigure the spacious interior to boost the considerably proportioned living spaces comprising large lounge room; which flows through an archway to sizable kitchen/meals and an internal laundry easily adapted to extend the existing kitchen area or enlarge the dimensions of the bathroom.
A peaceful rear courtyard provides privacy and quietude with the added utility of a workshop and shed on premises.
Huge bedrooms include a toilet ensuite to the master; with everything in place for a sympathetic makeover.
Includes a 600mm Euromaid oven, ceiling fans, split system air conditioning, and Vulcan wall heater.
Offering immense appeal for renovators and investors alike, the excellent position of this property also allows easy access to the CBD via CityLink.
Insights: 11 Collins Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.
